Working with DICOM Color and B&W images

See What is a non-capturing group in regular expressions?.

# kind = "image_base|nifti_color|dicom_color"
kind = "image_base|dicom_color"

splitter = glue::glue(
  # "^(5_images)/([0-9]+)/({kind})(:?/.*/.*)?/.*\\.(?:img|dcm)$"
  "^(5_images)/([0-9]+)/({kind})/.*\\.(?:img|dcm)$"
)
column_names = c("series", "inumber", "kind")

NOTE 1: Debug the regexp with stringr::str_view.

NOTE 2: https://www.garrickadenbuie.com/project/regexplain/[RegExplain] – Regular expressions are tricky. RegExplain makes it easier to see what you’re doing.

library(purrr)  # %>%, compose

base_images = list.files(
  path = "5_images",
  pattern = ".*\\.(img|dcm)$",
  full.names = TRUE,
  recursive = TRUE
) %>%
  stringr::str_subset(kind)

info = nifti_info(
    base_images, into = column_names, regex = splitter
  ) %>%
  dplyr::select(
    series, inumber, kind, `x×y×z`, `pixel resolution [mm]`, file_name
  ) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(inumber, kind)
# info
info %>% dplyr::select(-file_name)

Our sample data: 10 DICOM multichannel images

dicom_info <- info %>% dplyr::filter(kind == "dicom_color")
dicom_plots = map(dicom_info$file_name, plotColorDICOM)

base_info <- info %>% dplyr::filter(kind == "image_base")
base_plots = map(base_info$file_name, plotColorDICOM)
